==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Zoogloea
<hw>Zo`o*gloe"a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., from Gr.
<grk>zw^,on</grk> an animal + <?/ any glutinous substance.]</ety>
<fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>A colony or mass of bacteria imbedded in a
viscous gelatinous substance. The zoogloea is characteristic of a
transitory stage through which rapidly multiplying bacteria pass in the
course of their evolution. Also used adjectively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

